author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Men's soccer | ODU pair honored
text:
Old Dominion's Ivan Militar shared Conference USA Offensive Player of the Week honors in men's soccer with Kentucky's Napo Matsoso. The Monarchs' David Macsicza was Defensive Player of the Week after scoring the game-winning goal and anchoring a defense that shut out New Mexico.
Militar had a goal and an assist in No. 11 ODU's win over the Lobos. The Monarchs, unbeaten in their past eight matches, play a C-USA match at Florida International at 7 p.m. Saturday.
